# Phase Details — Database & Backend Specifications

## Phase 1 — Database Schema

### 1.1 Tables (Neon Postgres)

Write migrations as raw SQL in `db/migrations/`.

#### bookings
```sql
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS bookings (
  id            UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  name          VARCHAR(100)   NOT NULL,
  email         VARCHAR(254)   NOT NULL,
  phone         VARCHAR(20)    NOT NULL,
  service       VARCHAR(100)   NOT NULL,
  preferred_date DATE,
  message       TEXT,
  postcode      VARCHAR(10),
  status        VARCHAR(20)    NOT NULL DEFAULT 'new',
  source        VARCHAR(50)    DEFAULT 'website',
  created_at    TIMESTAMPTZ    NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW(),
  updated_at    TIMESTAMPTZ    NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW()
);
```

#### leads
```sql
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS leads (
  id            UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  name          VARCHAR(100)   NOT NULL,
  email         VARCHAR(254)   NOT NULL,
  phone         VARCHAR(20),
  message       TEXT           NOT NULL,
  page_source   VARCHAR(200),
  status        VARCHAR(20)    NOT NULL DEFAULT 'new',
  created_at    TIMESTAMPTZ    NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW()
);
```

#### reviews
```sql
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS reviews (
  id            UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  reviewer_name VARCHAR(100)   NOT NULL,
  area          VARCHAR(100),
  service       VARCHAR(100),
  rating        SMALLINT       NOT NULL CHECK (rating BETWEEN 1 AND 5),
  review_text   TEXT           NOT NULL,
  review_date   DATE           NOT NULL,
  platform      VARCHAR(50)    DEFAULT 'google',
  verified      BOOLEAN        DEFAULT FALSE,
  published     BOOLEAN        DEFAULT TRUE,
  created_at    TIMESTAMPTZ    NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW()
);
```

#### blog_posts
```sql
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS blog_posts (
  id            UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  slug          VARCHAR(200)   NOT NULL UNIQUE,
  title         VARCHAR(300)   NOT NULL,
  excerpt       TEXT           NOT NULL,
  body          TEXT           NOT NULL,
  author        VARCHAR(100)   DEFAULT 'Peterborough Plumbers',
  featured_image VARCHAR(500),
  tags          TEXT[],
  published     BOOLEAN        DEFAULT FALSE,
  published_at  TIMESTAMPTZ,
  created_at    TIMESTAMPTZ    NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW(),
  updated_at    TIMESTAMPTZ    NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW()
);
```

#### analytics_events
```sql
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS analytics_events (
  id            UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  event_name    VARCHAR(100)   NOT NULL,
  page_path     VARCHAR(500),
  session_id    VARCHAR(100),
  metadata      JSONB,
  created_at    TIMESTAMPTZ    NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW()
);
```

#### Indexes
```sql
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_bookings_status     ON bookings(status);
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_bookings_created    ON bookings(created_at DESC);
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_reviews_published   ON reviews(published) WHERE published = TRUE;
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_blog_posts_slug     ON blog_posts(slug);
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_blog_published      ON blog_posts(published, published_at DESC);
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_analytics_event     ON analytics_events(event_name, created_at DESC);
```

### 1.2 Migration Runner (`db/migrate.ts`)

```typescript
import { sql } from '@/lib/db'
import fs from 'fs'
import path from 'path'

const migrationsDir = path.join(process.cwd(), 'db/migrations')
const files = fs.readdirSync(migrationsDir).filter(f => f.endsWith('.sql')).sort()

for (const file of files) {
  const migration = fs.readFileSync(path.join(migrationsDir, file), 'utf8')
  console.log(`Running migration: ${file}`)
  await sql.query(migration)
  console.log(`Done: ${file}`)
}
```

Run: `npx tsx db/migrate.ts`

### 1.3 Seed Data (`db/seed.ts`)

Seed the reviews table with real reviews from `content/reviews.ts` so the DB becomes single source of truth.

### 1.4 DB Utility Layer

Create typed query helpers in `lib/db/`:

```
lib/db/
  bookings.ts   — createBooking(), getBookings(), updateBookingStatus()
  leads.ts      — createLead(), getLeads()
  reviews.ts    — getPublishedReviews(), getAggregateRating()
  blog.ts       — getPublishedPosts(), getPostBySlug()
  analytics.ts  — trackEvent()
```

Each function must use tagged template literals, have TypeScript return types, handle errors with clear messages, and never log sensitive data.

